<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Zeb</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-21 17:13:33</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Of all the times I've camped this guy, and out of all <BR>
the information I've heard, the AC in Sro is less "rare"<BR>
than the one in OOT. I've camped the one in OOT 3 times <BR>
for 12 hours each... I've never.. NEVER.. seen him im OOT.<BR>
In Sro, if you're under lvl 44, and not a caster, good luck. The pure<BR>
casters have the best chance of taking the kill.  I've seen<BR>
that thing at least 7 times there in a 2 week period..<BR>
The best way (I think) to get him to spawn in Sro is just to<BR>
kill everything that moves. People have said the undead<BR>
are AC ph's, that spiders are SG ph's or the terrorantula ph's<BR>
and that the crypt mummies are AC ph's. Me personally, I think<BR>
everything in the zone has some sort of impact on the AC spawn.<BR>
Just run around and kill everything... most people who camp <BR>
this thing don't do that.. they just sit there. THOSE are the <BR>
people who complain about the damn thing taking 8+ hours to <BR>
spawn. Going back to the undead thing... all the undead are <BR>
24 hour (game time) spawns. Heres a little trick I've tried <BR>
and it seemed to work just about every time I did it.<BR>
- dont kill any undead for 2 game time days so they all spawn.<BR>
- kill them all at once starting at 8am<BR>
- then the next day, you have that many more chances for<BR>
the AC to spawn cause all the spots are open at once.<BR>
When I did this 4 Sgs spawned all at the same time which <BR>
makes you think.. <BR>
Gluck to yas..<BR>
